look.title: Top Downloaded Clicks
look.description: A table of Download File, Download count, and percent of total downloads, ordered by Download Count.

dashboard_elements.note_text:
A Download click shows the count that users have clicked to download an asset linked to on your page. 

The asset is a file type that is likely to be downloaded versus being viewed in a browser. Example assets include: .pdf, .xls, .xlsx, .doc, .docx, .ppt, etc.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html:
A Download click shows the count that users have clicked to download an asset linked to on your page. 

The asset is a file type that is likely to be downloaded versus being viewed in a browser. Example assets include: .pdf, .xls, .xlsx, .doc, .docx, .ppt, etc.

look.title: Top Landing Page
look.description: A bar graph of Landing pages by their page view count, ordered by page view count descending.

dashboard_elements.note_text: The web page on the website that a user first visits during a session.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: The web page on the website that a user first visits during a session.

look.title: Top Offsite Links
look.description: A table of Offsite Link, and count of clicks ordered by clicks descending.

dashboard_elements.note_text: An Offsite link click on your page is a click on a URL link that does not contain your website's domain.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: An Offsite link click on your page is a click on a URL link that does not contain your website's domain.

look.title: Top Site Search Terms
look.description: A table of Search Term and Search Count ordered by Search Count.

dashboard_elements.note_text: Displays the phrases and the number of its searches within the site's search box which led the user to a page within the site.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: Displays the phrases and the number of its searches within the site's search box which led the user to a page within the site.

look.title: Page Views by Traffic Channel
look.description:
A stacked bar graph of referrals by medium (email, internal, search, social, unknown, or NULL). 

Requires a page view start date filter to return results.

Note: This is the page views version, for the sessions version see: https://analytics.gov.bc.ca/looks/275

dashboard_elements.note_text: An indicator of where traffic to the website/web page comes from. Traffic channels are separated into a number of groups. For details about the different traffic channels, please visit the Glossary.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: An indicator of where traffic to the website/web page comes from. Traffic channels are separated into a number of groups. For details about the different traffic channels, please visit the Glossary.

look.title: Top Pages
look.description: A table of the top pages by page view count, showing page title, page URL and page view count.

dashboard_elements.note_text: Displays the top performing pages based on page view count.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: Displays the top performing pages based on page view count.

look.title: Top Referrer URL Hosts
look.description:
A clustered bar graph showing referrers with a session count dimension and a percent of referrals dimension, ordered by session count descending.

Note: this version uses the Page Views table. For the sessions version see: https://analytics.gov.bc.ca/looks/290

dashboard_elements.note_text:
Users landing on the website/web page from other websites, search engines, etc.

If you see this result "statics.teams.cdn.office.net", the referrer is coming from a Microsoft Teams environment.

For example, you shared the website link in a Teams chat, and folks are clicking on that link.
